One cleric with infinite mana COULD keep the MT up in this fight, assuming he times heals perfectly, never gets hit with the AE and the mob stays slowed. I would strongly advise against that though LOL. I'd recommend 3-4 clerics minimum just to keep it safe, or 2-3 clerics and a ton of mod rods. This beast is a pretty long fight, but really not that difficult.<br>
<br>
Rhag1: Easy fight, 2-3 clerics. We killed him with 3 groups but could easily have done it with 2.<br>
<br>
Rhag2: Celest or Remove Curse both deal pretty easily with the DoT, just make sure someone stays on top of it. The damn monk that forgot to tell me he was cursed kinda ticked me off wasting my mana with heals when I could have cured him. I noticed the curse on the caster more quickly since they shouldn't be taking any damage.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzxing.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zxing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/10/02 4:21:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9657.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rhag's and Thought Horror Overfiend!</span><hr size=1> Yes, people that don't ask for cures right away, if they get cursed, deserve to die from it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
